At the start of the year, we collaborated closely with Fraud Tech and CRH to elevate the Line of Business (LOB) experience on the DQ4QD platform. Building on that momentum, we subsequently partnered with 11 additional clients, working to understand their unique requirements and challenges, implementing tailored solutions, and continuously refining the platform’s usability and functionality to meet their evolving needs.

We are actively engaging with various partner teams—such as the ITC Hadoop team for technical harvest, the EpiCenter team for both business and technical metadata, and multiple TechADS teams for business metadata, AIT/AIF details, and trend data. Additionally, we are working with the OneHadoop and Hyper Ingestion teams to capture and leverage trend data effectively.

We are collaborating with multiple teams and LOBs to highlight our strategic approach and capabilities within the Data Catalog system. By demonstrating key features, showcasing data discovery tools, and illustrating how effective metadata management can improve overall data governance, we aim to encourage wider adoption and unlock maximum value from our cataloging initiatives.

We have formed a partnership with technology executives to disseminate in-depth knowledge about the Strategic Data Platform (SDP) and to promote the use of DQ4QD and DCM tools. This includes conducting training sessions, developing comprehensive resources, and nurturing a continuous learning environment—ensuring that all stakeholders understand the full potential and advantages of these cutting-edge data solutions.

