Collaborated with multiple teams to design and build the DQ4QD platform, capturing a broad range of requirements and integrating them into a unified solution. This effort has led to the successful onboarding of over 11 teams and more than 1,700 DQ checks, effectively meeting diverse business needs.

Transformed the DQ4QD platform into a self-service solution by automating various operations—such as the migration utility, onboarding procedures, and job tracking—significantly reducing manual intervention and improving overall efficiency.

Enhanced both the user and developer experience by introducing advanced tracking capabilities, refining existing features (including rule version management and DAG versioning), and streamlining the onboarding portal. Additionally, we expanded support to multiple lines of business across DEV, SIT, UAT, and workspace environments, and integrated connectors for Pega, Object Storage, and MongoDB, enabling greater flexibility and scalability.

Successfully completed a proof of concept (POC) for real-time data quality checks on Kafka consumer streaming data, ensuring immediate monitoring, validation, and integrity of high-velocity data streams.

At the start of the year, participated in innovation forums and submitted two proposals aimed at further enhancing our data quality processes and tools, underscoring our ongoing commitment to continuous improvement.


------
We have developed extensive monitoring dashboards for the consumer platform, introducing comprehensive reporting and a range of alerting systems for the DQ4QD platform—such as job execution tracking, file compaction monitoring, and a DQ check dashboard. These enhancements offer real-time visibility and immediate alerts on potential issues, significantly improving overall system reliability.

We have bolstered platform availability and performance by reviewing and fine-tuning the underlying architecture, ensuring that it meets the DQ4QD system’s defined Recovery Time Objectives (RTO) and Recovery Point Objectives (RPO).

We have sustained a zero-data-loss streaming platform that continuously synchronizes data from Kafka to HDFS, and by integrating multiple connectors (including those for RDBMS systems), we have strengthened both data integration and reliability.

We have consistently maintained uninterrupted platform availability for Kafka consumers, DCM, and DQ4QD, ensuring a seamless and reliable experience for all users.

We are currently developing a dedicated user support ticketing and issue resolution system for the DQ4QD platform. This initiative will streamline support processes, accelerate response times, and enhance overall user satisfaction.


